{{Quote|I am ''Sister Domina...'' priestess in the ''Order of the Sacred Circle.'' We have risked violating the Imperial blockade to seek your ''council...'' and, perhaps, your ''aid''.|Domina Tagge|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 35">[[Star Wars (1977) 35|''Star Wars'' (1977) 35]]</ref>}}
'''''Star Wars 35: Dark Lord's Gambit''''' is the thirty-fifth issue in the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] series of comics.

==Plot summary==
[[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] finally learns the name of the boy who destroyed the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star I]], and sets a plan in motion to get his revenge. He enlists the aid of [[General/Legends|General]] [[Ulric Tagge/Legends|Ulric Tagge]] as well as his younger sister Sister [[Domina Tagge/Legends|Domina Tagge]] to help him in the endeavor. Domina is a member of the [[Order of the Sacred Circle]] who have thus far remained neutral in the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], but that will soon change and each side in the conflict will send a single envoy to [[Monastery/Legends|Monastery]] to present his case. Vader is to represent the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and Domina ensures that the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]] would send [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] as their representative. However, [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han]] travel to the system in the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] and orbit Monastery and monitor Luke's activities through [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] who accompanied Luke on the mission. While Luke thinks he may be in over his head on this diplomatic mission, Domina reassures him even though her true intentions are revenge for Luke's involvement in the apparent death of [[Orman Tagge/Legends|Orman Tagge]].

==Continuity==
Vader discovers that it was "Luke" Skywalker who destroyed the Death Star. Up until this point both chronologically and as part of the publishing schedule, Vader was only aware that "Skywalker" was responsible.

[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] pilots an [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|T-65 X-wing starfighter]] for the first time in the comic series since the adaptation of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']]; his call sign is [[Blue Leader/Legends|Blue Leader]].

Luke is wearing something other than his traditional "farm boy" outfit for the first time since the movie adaptation as this time we see him dressed in the same outfit that he wore during the medal ceremony in ''A New Hope''.

Leia's injured leg is referenced in events described in [[Alan Moore]]'s "[[Tilotny Throws a Shape]]" published in ''[[The Empire Strikes Back Monthly]] [[The Empire Strikes Back Monthly 154|#154]]''.

